{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/505", "repo": "rails", "body": "@mikekelly No, I don't know of any implementations off the top of my head. As for idempotent PUTs, the problem is *precisely* that clients assume the idempotent properties of PUT, but the server might not do idempotent updates in PUT.\r\n\r\n@exviva I agree. But I think there should be some sort of transitional stage in 3.x that introduces devs to PATCH and allows them to opt-in before Rails 4.", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f14bd3543c151012144"}, "issue_id": 505, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3183998", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/505#issuecomment-3183998", "updated_at": "2011-12-16T22:59:50Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee", "login": "dlee", "gravatar_id": "139de3f8c3d6ee008cdb3abd3da23908", "html_url": "https://github.com/dlee", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/139de3f8c3d6ee008cdb3abd3da23908?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F80177fe965b78111f4dfee80cfdc3689.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 7035, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-12-16T22:59:50Z", "id": 3183998, "owner": "rails"}
